Dear Unattach user,

*Unattach 3.1.0 has been released!*

As an existing user, you can get it at 50% discount
<https://unattach.app/?promo=3Dprev3&utm_source=3Drelease&utm_medium=3Demai=
l&utm_campaign=3Demail31#get>
(expires in 7 days).

What's new?

   - *Fixed the 500 results limit.* Finally found and fixed the elusive bug
   that prevented more than 500 search results. The results table will now
   show all emails matching the search query.
   - *Updated code license.* The license for the source code has changed
   from GPL 3 <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html> to a shared
   source license
   <https://github.com/rokstrnisa/unattach/blob/v3.1.0/LICENSE>.
   - *Removed most donation buttons.* The sign-in screen no longer shows
   donation buttons. Similarly, the occasional pop-up has been removed. The
   donation menu in the main view remains.
   - *Automatic sign-in.* After signing in, you can check "Sign in
   automatically" in the Settings menu. This skips the sign-in screen if th=
e
   authorization token is still valid.
   - *Minor improvements.*
      - Vertically compacted the main view to allow for smaller screens.
      - Added a setting for changing the date format used for the Date
      column.
      - "Subscribe to updates" checkbox setting is now persisted.
      - The results table now optionally also shows the email receivers and
      attachments.
      - Added FROM_NAME_OR_EMAIL to filename schema variables, which shows
      the sender's name if present, their email otherwise.
      - Show a warning if the filename schema doesn't end with the
      attachment name.
      - Improved wording on the labels filter, changed wording for email
      metadata, renamed IGNORED email state to NOT_SELECTED state, and rena=
med
      the Note column to Process Log.
      - Made logging more verbose. You can view the log through Help menu >
      Open log file.
   - *Bug fixes.*
      - Removed a slow memory leak. See if you can spot it in the code
      change
      <https://github.com/rokstrnisa/unattach/commit/bc2227820bdce0397f0248=
488fb2de51519966f1>
      .
      - Backing up an email no longer fails if the target directory doesn't
      exist.
      - The "Open" link in the results table works correctly after removing
      the email's attachment.
      - Processing no longer fails when an email doesn't have valid body
      parts.
   - *Code cleanup.* A large re-architecture and cleanup of the code that
   allows for simulating Gmail APIs for development testing purposes. This
   included switching to Java 15. Added a mini-tool for pretty-printing
   MimeMessages.

The website now also contains a list of Frequently Asked Questions
<https://unattach.app/faq>.

If you find any bugs, or have suggestions on improving the app, please
reply to this email, use the feedback system in the app itself, or
submit a GitHub
issue <https://github.com/rokstrnisa/unattach/issues>.

You can find Unattach also on Twitter <https://twitter.com/UnattachApp>,
Facebook <https://www.facebook.com/Unattach>, and YouTube
